   <tr>
      <td>It was in high school that I formed my first band.  I started out on rhythm guitar, but like most new bands we had to have a bass, so I became a bass guitarist.  Eventually my co-founders all left for college and 8to 5 jobs.  I continued playing with several different bands and spent years on the road traveling to gigs in the Northwest and Canada. After settling down to marriage, a family, and an 8 to 5, I stopped playing and sold all my gear.  About eight years ago I was introduced to “Olde School”, and have enjoyed getting back into music once again.</td>
