   <tr>
      <td><center>Charlie Beecroft – Rhythm Guitar and Vocals</center></td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
      <td><center><%= image_tag 'cb.png' %></center></td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
      <td>Charlie started the Olde School Band in 2004 while working at Mountain View Middle School to play at community events and fundraisers. He had played in similar bands while teaching at Department of Defense Schools in Germany and Japan from 1989-2001 and missed that weekly “rock and roll therapy”. Charlie played the guitar off and on since he was in 7th grade with the heaviest playing years in the 1970’s while in the army and since the 1990’s when he started playing in bands. In the early days he played a 12 string and sang quite a bit of folk and country mixed with songs from Simon and Garfunkel, Crosby Stills Nash and Young, Dylan, and others. His friend and bandmate Dave convinced him to buy his Epiphone Casino in 1999 which was better suited to some of the rhythm and blues and rock they were playing at the time. Charlie does vocals on songs from the Eagles, Stones, The Band, and a variety of other artists from the 60’s though the 90’s. Charlie always says, “I bought a PA and surround myself with people with a lot more talent than I have so I get to play and have fun.” And fun is what it is all about.</td>
   </tr>
