   <tr>
      <td><center>Liz Zanze - Sax, Flute and Vocals</center></td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
      <td><center><%= image_tag 'photoliz.png' %></center></td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
      <td><p>Liz Zanze grew up playing the flute, starting at the age of 10.  She lived with her family in San Jose and was able to play in several groups through high school.  She traveled to Japan with the San Jose Youth Symphony in 1972 and enjoyed performing with the orchestra.  Liz went to SF State to complete her BA in music, and she loved going to the jazz clubs in the City and taking in all of the culture.  Liz  started playing music in the Bay Area back in 1976, playing in big bands that performed in San Francisco.  She played in a big band led by a leader named Nick Jordan, who would later become his boss.  Liz was often the only girl in the band and had a tuxedo outfit she would wear to the gigs.</p>
          <br>
          <p>Liz moved to the Sacramento area with her husband Brian in the early 80’s, joining rock bands that included the all girl band,  NoBoy and jazz duo called Take Five.    Liz studied the flute and saxophone through college and began playing the bass in the early 1980’s.  She enjoys playing rock, jazz and classical music and is happiest when she is jamming  with her friends.  Liz teaches music in the Redding area and participates in several bands and ensembles in Redding.    She currently plays jazz with the Shasta College Jazz Band and Dick Turners “Fever” jazz septet  and classic rock n’ roll with Olde School.  Playing music is a blast!</p>
      </td>
   </tr>
