   <tr>
      <td>Peter grew up playing guitar singing Beatles and Stones and writing his own songs. Raising a family as a full time teacher, he continued his guitar playing on Sundays in Church. All of his son are musicians, so when Charlie asked him if he knew of any drummers, Peter said," Well I have a drum set in the garage, I could learn to keep a beat on skins." And that is how it happened. The guitar player became a drummer and the rest is history. Well, not much history, yet.</td>
   </tr>
